OL,3,GWales
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FMostly cloudy and dry today.
OL,6,FCloud may thin and break a little at
OL,7,Ftimes to give some brighter spells.
OL,8,FHowever, where the cloud thickens
OL,9,Fthere could be a few spots of drizzle.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FStaying largely cloudy this
OL,12,Fevening and tonight with an increasing
OL,13,Fchance of drizzly outbreaks.
OL,14,FThickening cloud will hold
OL,15,Ftemperatures up above freezing.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FA grey, cloudy and damp
OL,18,Fstart at first. However, cloud will
OL,19,Fgradually lift and break a little into
OL,20,Fthe afternoon, giving some bright or
OL,21,Fsunny spells at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
